pl.touk.hades.sql.timemonitoring
Class SqlTimeBasedLoadFactory

java.lang.Object
  pl.touk.hades.sql.timemonitoring.SqlTimeBasedLoadFactory
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class SqlTimeBasedLoadFactory
extends Object
implements Serializable

A factory that produces an instance of Load class when given a pair of numeric values: the main database load and the failover database load. Such a numeric pair is transformed into a load (which is descriptive rather than numeric) as follows. Each factory holds two numeric values: sqlTimeTriggeringFailbackNanos and statementExecutionTimeLimitTriggeringFailbackNanos (which can be set in SqlTimeBasedLoadFactory(long, long)), where the first value must not be less than the second value. Numeric values not greater than statementExecutionTimeLimitTriggeringFailbackNanos indicate low load level. Numeric values greater than statementExecutionTimeLimitTriggeringFailbackNanos and not greater than sqlTimeTriggeringFailbackNanos indicate medium load level. Numeric values greater than sqlTimeTriggeringFailbackNanos and less than Long.MAX_VALUE indicate high load level. Numeric values greater than or equal to ExceptionEnum.minErroneousValue() indicate exceptionWileMeasuring load level.

Author:
Michal Sokolowski
